### 3.2.5 Analytical Matrix — Parcelable Marshalling Order

| Order | Sender (`writeToParcel`) | Receiver (`Parcel in` constructor) | Type |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | `dest.writeInt(id)` | `in.readInt()` | `int` |
| 2 | `dest.writeString(name)` | `in.readString()` | `String` |
| 3 | `dest.writeString(type)` | `in.readString()` | `String` |
| 4 | `dest.writeFloat(currentValue)` | `in.readFloat()` | `float` |
| 5 | `dest.writeByte(...)` | `in.readByte()` | `byte` (for boolean) |

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Mistake (KTU exam pitfall):** The order of `writeXxx` in `writeToParcel()` MUST exactly match the order of `readXxx` in the parcel constructor. Mismatched order silently corrupts data (e.g., reading an `int` as a `String` will throw `ClassCastException` deep in the framework — hard to debug).

