## 3.3 Walkthrough C — Returning Data from a Child Activity (Modern ActivityResultLauncher)

### 3.3.1 The Scenario

`MainActivity` opens `ConfigActivity` to let the user select a Wi-Fi SSID. `ConfigActivity` must *return* the selected SSID back to `MainActivity`.

### 3.3.2 Sender Side — MainActivity (Modern Approach, 2024)

```java
import androidx.activity.result.ActivityResultLauncher;
import androidx.activity.result.contract.ActivityResultContracts;

private final ActivityResultLauncher<Intent> configLauncher =
    registerForActivityResult(
        new ActivityResultContracts.StartActivityForResult(),
        result -> {
            if (result.getResultCode() == RESULT_OK && result.getData() != null) {
                Intent data = result.getData();
                String ssid = data.getStringExtra("SELECTED_SSID");
                Log.d("MainActivity", "User selected SSID: " + ssid);
            }
        }
    );

private void openConfig() {
    Intent intent = new Intent(this, ConfigActivity.class);
    intent.putExtra("DEVICE_ID", "ESP32-A4:CF:12");
    configLauncher.launch(intent);  // Modern replacement for startActivityForResult
}
```

### 3.3.3 Receiver Side — ConfigActivity

```java
private void finishWithSelection(String ssid) {
    Intent resultIntent = new Intent();
    resultIntent.putExtra("SELECTED_SSID", ssid);
    setResult(RESULT_OK, resultIntent);
    finish();
}
```

### 3.3.4 Why the Modern API? (Conceptual)

> [!NOTE]
> `startActivityForResult()` and `onActivityResult()` were **deprecated in AndroidX Activity 1.2.0 (2020)**. The KTU 2024 syllabus accepts both APIs in exam answers, but full marks require mentioning the `ActivityResultLauncher` approach as the modern, lifecycle-safe alternative. The new API survives configuration changes (e.g., device rotation) without losing pending results.

