## 3.4 Walkthrough D — Passing Data via Implicit Intents (IoT Cloud Trigger)

### 3.4.1 Use Case

User taps a "Share Telemetry" button in the app. The app must launch *any* installed app capable of handling `ACTION_SEND` with text/plain MIME (e.g., WhatsApp, Gmail, Slack) and prefill the telemetry JSON.

### 3.4.2 The Code

```java
private void shareTelemetry(String telemetryJson) {
    Intent shareIntent = new Intent(Intent.ACTION_SEND);
    shareIntent.setType("text/plain");
    shareIntent.putExtra(Intent.EXTRA_TEXT, telemetryJson);
    shareIntent.putExtra(Intent.EXTRA_SUBJECT, "IoT Sensor Telemetry Snapshot");

    // Optional: title shown in the chooser dialog
    String chooserTitle = "Share telemetry via...";
    Intent chooser = Intent.createChooser(shareIntent, chooserTitle);

    // Best practice: pass new task flag only if launching from a non-Activity context
    if (getPackageManager().resolveActivity(shareIntent, 0) != null) {
        startActivity(chooser);
    } else {
        Toast.makeText(this, "No app available to handle share", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
    }
}
```

### 3.4.3 What Makes It "Implicit"?

- **No `ComponentName` is set.** Only the action (`ACTION_SEND`), type (`text/plain`), and extras.
- The **Android PackageManager** queries all installed apps for an `<intent-filter>` matching `android.intent.action.SEND` + `text/plain`.
- If multiple match, the system shows a **chooser dialog**.
- If none match, `startActivity()` throws `ActivityNotFoundException` (unless `resolveActivity()` is checked first, as in the snippet above).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **KTU 2024 Trap Question:** *"Can implicit Intents target a specific component by name?"*
> **Answer:** No. Implicit Intents rely on intent filters for resolution. Use **Explicit Intents** (`new Intent(context, TargetClass.class)`) when you know the exact target.

