## 3.5 Comparative Decision Matrix — Which Passing Method to Use?

| Scenario | Best Method | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Pass a username between two known activities | Explicit Intent + `putExtra(String, String)` | Simple, type-safe, low overhead |
| Pass a custom sensor object | Parcelable + `putParcelableArrayListExtra` | Zero reflection, fast marshalling |
| Pass a `HashMap<String, Object>` | Serializable or convert to JSON String | `Bundle` doesn't support raw `HashMap` |
| Pass a large JSON (> 100 KB) | Write to file/cache + pass URI | Avoids Binder transaction limit |
| Return a value from a child activity | `ActivityResultLauncher` + `setResult()` | Lifecycle-safe modern API |
| Trigger an external app (share, dial, view URL) | Implicit Intent | Lets the system pick the best handler |
| Stream continuous data (e.g., live sensor feed) | Bound Service / LiveData / Flow | Intents are one-shot, not streaming |
| Send a command to a long-running Service | Intent + `startService()` / `bindService()` | Service stays alive beyond the activity |

