### Question 1 [KTU University Exam - May 2024 Style]
> **Q: Define an Android Intent. Explain the role of "extras" in passing data between activities with a suitable example. (3 marks) — [BT Level: Remember/Understand]**

**Model Answer (3 points to be explicitly written):**

1. **(1 mark) Definition:** An Intent is a messaging object (`android.content.Intent`) used to request an action from another app component. It is the fundamental mechanism for inter-component communication in Android.

2. **(1 mark) Role of Extras:** Extras are **key-value pairs** stored in a `Bundle` attached to the Intent. They allow the sending activity to pass supplementary data (e.g., user ID, sensor value) to the receiving activity, which reads them via `getXxxExtra()` methods.

3. **(1 mark) Example:** `intent.putExtra("USER_NAME", "admin");` on the sender side, and `String name = getIntent().getStringExtra("USER_NAME");` on the receiver side.

---

### Question 2 [KTU University Exam - Dec 2023 Style]
> **Q: Differentiate between Explicit and Implicit Intents in Android. (3 marks) — [BT Level: Understand]**

**Model Answer:**

| Aspect | Explicit Intent | Implicit Intent |
|---|---|---|
| **Target** | Specifies the target component by class name | Declares a general action; system resolves target |
| **Use Case** | In-app navigation (Activity → Activity) | Cross-app actions (share, dial, view) |
| **Construction** | `new Intent(ctx, TargetActivity.class)` | `new Intent("android.intent.action.VIEW")` |
| **Resolution** | Direct dispatch via `mComponent` | Intent filter matching via PackageManager |
| **Example** | Open `DashboardActivity` from `LoginActivity` | Open a URL in any browser |

**(3 marks — 1.5 marks for the table / correct 3 differences, 0.5 for a one-line example each.)**

