# 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

## 4.1 Broadcast Receiver — Complete Event Flow

The following Mermaid sequence diagram maps the **end-to-end broadcast lifecycle** for a typical IoT scenario (e.g., a temperature sensor pushing data to the app).

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Sensor as IoT Sensor / Backend Service
    participant Sender as Sender Component
    participant FW as Android Framework
    participant Manifest as Manifest Index
    participant Receiver as IoTDataReceiver
    participant UI as Activity / Notification

    Sensor->>Sender: Telemetry data arrives
    Sender->>Sender: Build Intent with extras
    Sender->>FW: sendBroadcast(intent)
    FW->>Manifest: Lookup registered filters
    Manifest-->>FW: Matching IoTDataReceiver found
    FW->>Receiver: Instantiate (if not alive)
    FW->>Receiver: onReceive(context, intent)
    alt Quick path (lightweight)
        Receiver->>UI: Toast / update View
    else Heavy path (DB / network)
        Receiver->>Receiver: goAsync() + spawn Thread
        Receiver->>Receiver: pendingResult.finish()
    end
    Receiver-->>FW: Return
    FW->>Receiver: Mark eligible for GC
```

## 4.2 Block-Level Functional Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Application Start] --> B{Registration Method?}
    B -- Static --> C[Declare in AndroidManifest.xml]
    B -- Dynamic --> D[Context.registerReceiver at Runtime]
    C --> E[Android Manifest Indexer]
    D --> F[Runtime Receiver Registry]
    E --> G{Intent Matches Filter?}
    F --> G
    G -- No --> H[Intent Discarded]
    G -- Yes --> I[Framework Instantiates Receiver]
    I --> J[onReceive Context Intent]
    J --> K{Workload Type?}
    K -- Lightweight --> L[Direct UI Update / Toast]
    K -- Heavy --> M[goAsync + Worker Thread]
    M --> N[Database / Network Operation]
    N --> O[pendingResult.finish]
    L --> P[Receiver Returned to GC]
    O --> P
```

## 4.3 Decision Tree — When to Use Static vs Dynamic Registration

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Start([New Broadcast Listener Needed]) --> Q1{Should it fire when app is killed?}
    Q1 -- Yes --> Q2{Is it a restricted Android 8+ implicit broadcast?}
    Q1 -- No --> Dyn[Use Dynamic Registration]
    Q2 -- Yes --> Q3{Is API 26+?}
    Q3 -- Yes --> Alt[Use JobScheduler or WorkManager]
    Q3 -- No --> Static[Use Static Manifest Registration]
    Q2 -- No --> Static
    Dyn --> Q4[Pair with onResume / onPause]
    Static --> Q5[Declare in AndroidManifest.xml]
    Alt --> Q6[Defer or use explicit broadcast]
    Q4 --> End([Done])
    Q5 --> End
    Q6 --> End
```
