## PART B — Full-Answer Questions (14 Marks Each, with Internal Choice)

### Question A — Option 1: `[KTU University Exam - Model Paper 2024, Adapted]`

**(a)** Explain the architecture of Content Providers in Android with a neat block diagram. Describe the role of `ContentResolver`, `UriMatcher`, and `ContentValues` in this architecture. **(7 marks)**

**(b)** Write a complete Android Java program to:
- Create a custom Content Provider named `StudentProvider` with authority `com.example.university.provider` and table `students` (columns: `_id`, `name`, `roll_no`, `cgpa`).
- Implement the four CRUD methods: `insert()`, `query()`, `update()`, and `delete()`.
- Demonstrate a client app that performs all four operations on this provider. **(7 marks)**

### Model Answer — Question A

#### Part (a) — Architecture Explanation (7 marks)

**Content Provider architecture** has three logical tiers:

**Tier 1 — Client Application**
- The client obtains a `ContentResolver` instance via `getContentResolver()`.
- It builds a **Content URI** (e.g., `content://com.example.university.provider/students`).
- It calls CRUD methods on the resolver, which in turn triggers IPC.

**Tier 2 — Android System (Binder)**
- The `ContentResolver` uses the system **Binder** to marshal the call across process boundaries.
- The system checks the **URI permissions** declared in the provider's manifest.
- If authorized, the call is forwarded to the target `ContentProvider` instance.

**Tier 3 — Provider Application**
- The provider's methods (`insert`, `query`, `update`, `delete`) are invoked.
- A **`UriMatcher`** is used to identify whether the URI refers to a collection or a specific row.
- A **`ContentValues`** object is the standard key-value container passed to `insert()` and `update()`.
- The actual data operation is performed on the backing store (typically SQLite).
- The provider then calls `notifyChange()` so that any registered observers refresh.

**Roles in summary:**

| Component | Role |
|---|---|
| `ContentResolver` | Client-side IPC bridge; one per context |
| `UriMatcher` | Server-side router mapping URI patterns to integer codes |
| `ContentValues` | Transport container for column values during insert/update |

*(Award 4 marks for diagram + tier explanation, 3 marks for component role table.)*

#### Part (b) — Code Implementation (7 marks)

**Step 1 — Manifest Declaration**

```xml
<provider
    android:name=".StudentProvider"
    android:authorities="com.example.university.provider"
    android:exported="false" />
```

**Step 2 — Contract Class**

```java
public final class StudentContract {
    public static final String AUTHORITY = "com.example.university.provider";
    public static final Uri CONTENT_URI =
            Uri.parse("content://" + AUTHORITY + "/students");

    public static final String COL_NAME    = "name";
    public static final String COL_ROLL_NO = "roll_no";
    public static final String COL_CGPA    = "cgpa";
}
```

**Step 3 — DB Helper**

```java
public class StudentDbHelper extends SQLiteOpenHelper {
    private static final String DB = "students.db";
    public StudentDbHelper(Context c) { super(c, DB, null, 1); }

    @Override public void onCreate(SQLiteDatabase db) {
        db.execSQL("CREATE TABLE students (" +
                   "_id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, " +
                   "name TEXT, roll_no TEXT, cgpa REAL);");
    }
    @Override public void onUpgrade(SQLiteDatabase db, int o, int n) {
        db.execSQL("DROP TABLE IF EXISTS students");
        onCreate(db);
    }
}
```

**Step 4 — Provider Class**

```java
public class StudentProvider extends ContentProvider {

    private StudentDbHelper dbHelper;
    private static final int STUDENTS = 1, STUDENT_ID = 2;
    private static final UriMatcher MATCHER = new UriMatcher(UriMatcher.NO_MATCH);

    static {
        MATCHER.addURI(StudentContract.AUTHORITY, "students", STUDENTS);
        MATCHER.addURI(StudentContract.AUTHORITY, "students/#", STUDENT_ID);
    }

    @Override public boolean onCreate() {
        dbHelper = new StudentDbHelper(getContext());
        return true;
    }

    @Override public Uri insert(Uri uri, ContentValues values) {
        long id = dbHelper.getWritableDatabase()
                          .insert("students", null, values);
        getContext().getContentResolver().notifyChange(uri, null);
        return ContentUris.withAppendedId(uri, id);
    }

    @Override public Cursor query(Uri uri, String[] proj, String sel,
                                  String[] selArgs, String sort) {
        SQLiteDatabase db = dbHelper.getReadableDatabase();
        if (MATCHER.match(uri) == STUDENT_ID) {
            sel = "_id=?";
            selArgs = new String[]{ String.valueOf(ContentUris.parseId(uri)) };
        }
        Cursor c = db.query("students", proj, sel, selArgs, null, null, sort);
        c.setNotificationUri(getContext().getContentResolver(), uri);
        return c;
    }

    @Override public int update(Uri uri, ContentValues cv, String sel,
                                String[] selArgs) {
        int n = dbHelper.getWritableDatabase()
                        .update("students", cv, sel, selArgs);
        if (n > 0) getContext().getContentResolver().notifyChange(uri, null);
        return n;
    }

    @Override public int delete(Uri uri, String sel, String[] selArgs) {
        int n = dbHelper.getWritableDatabase()
                        .delete("students", sel, selArgs);
        if (n > 0) getContext().getContentResolver().notifyChange(uri, null);
        return n;
    }

    @Override public String getType(Uri uri) { return null; }
}
```

**Step 5 — Client App Demo**

```java
public class MainActivity extends AppCompatActivity {
    @Override protected void onCreate(Bundle s) {
        super.onCreate(s);
        ContentResolver r = getContentResolver();

        // 1) INSERT
        ContentValues cv = new ContentValues();
        cv.put("name", "Anu");
        cv.put("roll_no", "KTU2024-101");
        cv.put("cgpa", 9.2);
        Uri u = r.insert(StudentContract.CONTENT_URI, cv);

        // 2) QUERY
        Cursor c = r.query(StudentContract.CONTENT_URI, null, null, null, null);
        while (c.moveToNext()) {
            Log.d("STUDENT", c.getString(c.getColumnIndexOrThrow("name")));
        }
        c.close();

        // 3) UPDATE
        ContentValues uv = new ContentValues();
        uv.put("cgpa", 9.5);
        r.update(StudentContract.CONTENT_URI, uv, "roll_no=?",
                 new String[]{"KTU2024-101"});

        // 4) DELETE
        r.delete(StudentContract.CONTENT_URI, "name=?",
                 new String[]{"Anu"});
    }
}
```

