### 2.3 KTU Formula Sheet / Cheat Sheet

> [!NOTE]
> The following table is a **conceptual cheat sheet**. There are no traditional "formulas" in mobile app development, but the **MQTT packet structure** and **latency budget** calculations are the closest analogue and appear frequently in KTU numerical questions.

| Concept | Expression / Value | Engineering Utility |
|---|---|---|
| MQTT Control Packet Types | `CONNECT (1)`, `CONNACK (2)`, `PUBLISH (3)`, `PUBACK (4)`, `SUBSCRIBE (8)`, `SUBACK (9)`, `PINGREQ (12)`, `DISCONNECT (14)` | Required for tracing Wireshark captures during lab viva |
| Fixed Header Size | **2 bytes minimum** (1 byte type+flags + 1 byte remaining length) | Defines the minimum overhead per packet |
| QoS 1 Dup Flag | Set to `1` on retransmit | Distinguishes a fresh message from a duplicate |
| **Round-Trip Latency Budget** | $T_{total} = T_{pub} + T_{broker} + T_{sub}$ | Used in viva to justify "real-time" claim; typically < 100 ms on LAN |
| **JSON Payload Size Constraint** | $P_{size} \leq 1 \text{ KB}$ | Mobile data conservation; larger payloads trigger `NetworkOnMainThreadException` |
| **Topic Wildcard `+`** | Matches a single level (e.g., `home/+/temp`) | Subscribe to all room temperatures |
| **Topic Wildcard `#`** | Matches multiple levels (e.g., `home/#`) | Subscribe to entire home sensor hierarchy |
| **Android Threading Rule** | Network I/O $\notin$ Main Thread | Enforced by `StrictMode.ThreadPolicy` since API 11 |
| **Paho Dependency** | `org.eclipse.paho:org.eclipse.paho.client.mqttv3:1.2.5` | Maven/Gradle coordinate — must be in `build.gradle` |
| **Permission Required** | `android.permission.INTERNET` | Declared in `AndroidManifest.xml` |

