### 4.2 MQTT Connection State Machine

The MQTT client transitions through these states. Understanding these is critical for diagnosing connection failures in the lab viva.

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> NEW
    NEW --> CONNECTING : connect called
    CONNECTING --> CONNECTED : CONNACK received
    CONNECTING --> DISCONNECTED : CONNACK with error code
    CONNECTED --> ACTIVE : subscribe and publish
    ACTIVE --> ACTIVE : PINGREQ PINGRESP handshake
    ACTIVE --> DISCONNECTED : keep-alive timeout 1.5 x interval
    ACTIVE --> DISCONNECTED : DISCONNECT packet sent
    DISCONNECTED --> CONNECTING : automatic reconnect
    DISCONNECTED --> [*] : app closed
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **State names in the diagram use plain uppercase text** (e.g., `ACTIVE`, `CONNECTED`) to comply with the Mermaid compilation safeguard rule that prohibits markdown formatting characters inside double-quoted labels.

