- [ ] The required library is **Eclipse Paho Android Service** — Maven coordinate `org.eclipse.paho:org.eclipse.paho.android.service:1.1.1`.
- [ ] The data interchange format is **JSON**, parsed using `org.json.JSONObject`. Never use XML.
- [ ] The manifest MUST declare `<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />`.
- [ ] On Android 9+, `usesCleartextTraffic="true"` is required for plaintext MQTT.
- [ ] The `MqttCallbackExtended` interface is implemented on the `Activity`; the `messageArrived()` callback runs on a **background thread** — always wrap UI updates in `runOnUiThread()`.
- [ ] **Client ID must be unique** — use `System.currentTimeMillis()` or `UUID.randomUUID()`.
- [ ] The MQTT topic hierarchy uses forward slashes: `ktu/lab/sensor/temp`.
- [ ] **Wildcards**: `+` matches one level, `#` matches multiple levels and must be the last character.
- [ ] **QoS 0** = fire-and-forget; **QoS 1** = PUBACK handshake; **QoS 2** = four-step handshake.
- [ ] **Keep-alive interval** is typically **60 seconds**; the broker drops the client if no PINGREQ arrives within 1.5× the interval.
- [ ] The **Last Will and Testament (LWT)** is a pre-registered message the broker publishes when it detects an unclean client disconnect.
- [ ] On the **device side (ESP8266)**, the Arduino `loop()` must call `client.loop()` to process incoming MQTT packets — this is NOT required on Android.
- [ ] The **three-tier architecture** is: Perception (sensor/actuator + MCU) → Network (MQTT broker :1883) → Application (Android UI + Paho client).
- [ ] The MQTT fixed header is **2 bytes minimum** (1 byte type+flags + 1 byte remaining length).
- [ ] **Wireshark filter for MQTT**: `mqtt` (lowercase, as the protocol is TCP-based and uses the dissector name `mqtt`).
- [ ] **Public test broker**: `test.mosquitto.org:1883` is used in labs; do NOT publish sensitive data here as it is open to the internet.
- [ ] The `cleanSession=false` option makes the broker persist subscriptions and missed messages (QoS 1+) for the client across reconnects.
